    "The use of meta classes is useful when we want to implement class behaviours before object (class) instantiation. Therefore, meta classes in some regards give us the same sorts of uses as decorators which are to manipulate or prep (classes) before the execution of them.\n",
    "\n",
    "To create a meta class we just create a class that, at the very least, needs to inherit from type."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "1f4cfed6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "10 100\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "class Meta(type):\n",
    "    def __new__(self,class_name,bases,attrs):\n",
    "        attrs[\"y\"] = 100\n",
    "        return type(class_name,bases,attrs) # instantiate / construct the class\n",
    "class Test(metaclass=Meta):x=10\n",
    "/print Test().x,Test().y"
   ]
  },
